reviews.review_text: Great sound! Great show.  This is an in-demand source.  Trust me on this.  Just take a listen, download if you like.

Brokedown Palace Ahhh...The decrepit antiquated crumbling friendly confines of Cal-Expo in SacTown. Saw the boys many, many times there including this show.They always delivered the goods here. Outdoor venue that probably held around 20,000. Plenty of room to roam around, dance or go sit for a while in the grand stand.This is a very nice sounding AUD and a strong show. Thanks Keith and the archive.
Cal Expo I think it held more like 8,000-10,000 it was easily the smallest place I saw the Dead

great not huge on the 90s but this show has a great set list and is well played all the way through, love the songs they play here, picasso great opener, the let it grow was good as well, the run at the start of set 2 is great and so is the run after drums, great high quality show the whole way through!

awesome encore too
